cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SD 

This paper deals with automatic visual speech recognition, which involves analyzing video data to recognize spoken phrases. This falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also uses unsupervised learning techniques and neural networks, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the paper applies a tandem GMM-HMM system, which is a common approach in speech recognition (cs.SD).
